<p>In the example above, we get all the <code class="highlighter-rouge">p</code> element except those which have the <code class="highlighter-rouge">highlight</code> class. Itâ€™s so nice, right? But if we wanted apply one more <em>filter</em> in the negation? Itâ€™s not possible. So, CSS level 4 give us this power.</p>

